The code chunk is part of the `undo()` method in the `ActionUpdateObjectProp` class, which manages undo functionality for object property updates in an editor.

def undo(self):
        print("Undo : updateObjectProp")
        if self.oldVal:
            self.obj[OG.OBJ_PROP][self.propName] = self.oldVal
            if self.undoFunc:
                self.undoFunc()
                if self.editor and self.fSelectObject:
                    base.direct.select(self.obj[OG.OBJ_NP], fUndo=0)
